42|37| who refrain from the greatest misdeeds and sexual offences, and forgive whenever they become angry, 
42|38| and who respond to their Lord and keep up prayer; and whose business is [conducted] through mutual consultation among themselves, and spend some of what We have provided them with, 
42|39| and who protect themselves whenever any outrage happens to them. 
42|40| The reward for an injury should be an injury proportionate to it. Yet anyone who overlooks things and becomes reconciled shall receive his payment from God; He does not love wrongdoers! 
42|41| Those who defend themselves after being wronged will have no way open against them; 
