89|15| Yet everyman says, whenever his Lord tests him by honoring and favoring him: "My Lord has honored me!"; 
89|16| while whenever He tests him by rationing His sustenance for him, he says: "My Lord has disgraced me." 
89|17| Rather you are not generous with the orphan 
89|18| nor do you promote feeding the needy, 
89|19| and greedily use up anything you inherit. 
89|20| You love money till it´s brimming over! 
89|21| Indeed when the earth has been completely flattened out 
89|22| and your Lord comes with the angels, row upon row, 
89|23| and brings up Hell on that day; on that day everyman will remember, as if remembrance even matters to him! 
89|24| He will say: "It´s too bad for me! What did I send on ahead during my lifetime?" 
89|25| On that day, no one will torment [anyone] with torment like His, 
89|26| and no one will hold to any agreement as he will hold to His! 
89|27| O Tranquil soul, 
89|28| return to your Lord well pleased and pleasing [Him]! 
89|29| Enter among My servants, 
89|30| and. enter My garden. 
90|1| I swear by [this] countryside, 
90|2| you are a native settled on this land 
90|3| as well as any parent and whatever he may father. 
90|4| We have created man under stress. 
90|5| Does he reckon that no one can do anything against him? 
90|6| He says: I have used up piles of money! 
90|7| Does he consider that no one sees him? 
90|8| Have We not granted him both eyes, 
90|9| a tongue and two lips, 
90|10| and guided him along both highroads? 
90|11| Yet he does not tackle the Obstacle! 
90|12| What will make you realize what the Obstacle is? 
90|13| [It means] redeeming the captive, 
90|14| or feeding 
90|15| some orphaned relative on a day of famine 
90|16| or some needy person in distress. 
90|17| Then he will act like someone who believes, recommends patience and encourages mercifulness. 
90|18| Those will be the companions on the right-hand side, 
90|19| while the ones who disbelieve in Our signs will be companions on the sinister side: 
90|20| above them a fire will hem them in. 
91|1| By the Sun and its radiance, 
91|2| and the moon as it trails after it, 
91|3| and daylight which shines resplendent from it, 
91|4| and night when it covers things up, 
91|5| and the sky and whatever built it, 
91|6| and the earth and what has stretched it out, 
91|7| and any soul and whatever has fashioned it 
91|8| and filled it with both its debauchery and its sense of duty! 
91|9| Anyone who purifies himself will prosper 
91|10| while whoever neglects to do so will be disappointed. 
91|11| Thamud rejected it through their arrogance 
91|12| when their meanest wretch was delegated 
91|13| and God´s messenger told them: "[Here is) God´s she-camel; give her its day to drink." 
91|14| They rejected him and mistreated her, so their Lord snarled at them because of their offence and leveled things off. 
91|15| He does not fear its outcome! 
92|1| By night as it broods, 
92|2| and daylight when things seem radiant, 
92|3| and whatever has created the male and the female, 
92|4| your effort has been too diffuse. 
92|5| For anyone who gives (generously], performs his duty 
92|6| and acts charitably in the finest manner 
92|7| We shall facilitate an easy way for him; 
92|8| while anyone who acts miserably, and feels he is self-sufficient 
92|9| and rejects the finest [things in life] 
92|10| We shall make it easy for him (to go] the hard way. 
92|11| His money will not help him out as he stumbles along. 
92|12| Guidance is Our concern: 
92|13| to Us belongs the Hereafter and the very First [of life]; 
92|14| so I have warned you (all) about a raging fire. 
92|15| Only the most wretched will roast in it, 
92|16| the one who rejects [the Message] and turns away; 
92|17| while the most heedful will keep away from it, 
92|18| the one who gives his money away and (thereby) purifies himself 
92|19| No one is awarded any favor by Him 
92|20| except through seeking the countenance of his Lord, the All-Highest.
92|21| [Such a man] shall meet approval. 
93|1| By the morning bright, 
93|2| and at night when all is still 
93|3| your Lord has not forsaken you nor is He annoyed. 
93|4| The Hereafter will be even better for you than the first [life] was. 
93|5| Your Lord will soon give you something which will leave you satisfied. 
93|6| Did He not find you an orphan and sheltered [you]? 
93|7| He found you lost and guided [you]. 
93|8| He found you destitute and made you rich! 
93|9| Thus the orphan must not be exploited; 
93|10| and the beggar should not be brushed aside. 
93|11| Still tell about your Lord´s favor. 
94|1| Did We not relieve your breast for you, 
94|2| and remove your burden from you 
94|3| that pressed down upon your back? 
94|4| We have even raised up renown of you! 
94|5| Yet hardship will bring ease. 
94|6| Indeed, hardship must bring ease! 
94|7| So whenever you have finished, still toil on! 
94|8| Towards your Lord direct your longing! 
95|1| By the Figtree and the Olive, 
95|2| Mount Sinai 
95|3| and this safe countryside, 
95|4| We have created man with the finest stature; 
95|5| then reduced him to the dregs on the bottom, 
95|6| except for those who believe and perform honorable deeds-their earnings shall never be withheld from them. 
95|7| What would make you reject religion later on? 
95|8| Is God not the Wisest of those who judge? 
96|1| READ in the name of your Lord Who creates, 
96|2| creates man from a clot! 
96|3| READ, for your Lord is most Generous; 
96|4| [it is He] Who teaches by means of the pen, 
96|5| teaches man what he does not know. 
96|6| However man acts so arrogant, 
96|7| for he considers he is self-sufficient. 
96|8| Yet to your Lord will be the Return! 
96|9| Have you seen someone who stops 
96|10| a worshipper as he prays? 
96|11| Have you considered whether he is [looking] for guidance 
96|12| or ordering heedfulness? 
96|13| Have you seen whether he has rejected [the message] and turned away? 
96|14| Does he not know that God sees [everything]? 
96|15| Of course not! Yet if he does not stop, We shall catch him by his forelock! 
96|16| Such a lying, sinful forelock! 
96|17| Let him appeal to his henchmen: 
96|18| We shall appeal to the avenging [angels]. 
96|19| Of course, do not obey him; bow down on your knees, and come closer! 
97|1| We have sent it down on the Night of Power! 
97|2| What will make you realize what the Night of Power is like? 
97|3| The Night of Power is better than a thousand months. 
97|4| Angels and the Spirit descend on it on every errand with their Lord´s permission; 
97|5| [it means] peace till the approach of daybreak. 
98|1| Those People of the Book who have disbelieved, plus the associators [of others with God] did not give up until evidence came to them, 
98|2| [through] a messenger from God reciting purified pages 
98|3| which comprise changeless books. 
98|4| Nor did those who were given the Book disagree (about it) until after evidence had come to them. 
98|5| Yet they have merely been ordered to worship God sincerely - [reserving] religion for Him [Alone], as righteous seekers [after Truth] and to keep up prayer and pay the welfare tax. That is the religion for an established [community]. 
98|6| Those People of the Book who disbelieve as well as the associators will remain in Hell fire; those are the worst creatures. 
98|7| Those who believe and perform honorable deeds are the best creatures; 
98|8| their reward from their Lord will be gardens of Eden through which rivers flow, to live in forever. God is pleased with them while they feel pleased with Him. That is [reserved] for anyone who dreads his Lord. 
99|1| When earth is shaken in her [final) quaking, 
99|2| and earth throws forth her burdens, 
99|3| and everyman says: "What is [happening] to her?" 
99|4| on that day she will report her news 
99|5| which your Lord has inspired her with. 
99|6| On that day men will appear in droves to be shown their actions; 
99|7| and whoever has done an atoms´ weight of good will see it; 
99|8| while whoever has done an atom´s weight of evil will see it. 
100|1| By the snorting chargers 
100|2| striking sparks [with their hooves] 
100|3| and racing [home] by morning, 
100|4| so they leave a trail of dust 
100|5| as they dash into the middle of the troops with it; 
100|6| everyman is grudging towards his Lord! 
100|7| He himself [acts] as a witness to that; 
100|8| and is quite passionate in his love of wealth. 
100|9| Does he not realize that when whatever [lies] in graves is tumbled out, 
100|10| and whatever is on [people´s] minds is checked up on, 
100|11| their Lord will be Informed about them on that day? 
101|1| The stunning [blow]! 
101|2| What is a disaster? 
101|3| What will make you realize something is going to stun [you]? 
101|4| Someday mankind will act like scattered moths 
101|5| and the mountains seem like tufts of yarn! 
101|6| So anyone whose scales are weighted down 
101|7| [will land] in pleasant living; 
101|8| while whoever´s scales are light 
101|9| will have a Pit to mother him. 
101|10| What will make you realize what this will be like? 
101|11| Scorching fire! 
102|1| Competition has distracted you 
102|2| until you visit graveyards. 
102|3| Nevertheless you soon will know; 
102|4| once more, you soon shall know! 
102|5| Of course, if you realized with absolute certainty 
102|6| how you will (all) see Hades, 
102|7| then you would see it with the [very] eye of certainty; 
102|8| next you will be questioned concerning bliss on that day. 
103|1| By eventide, everyman 
103|2| [feels] at a loss 
103|3| except for those who believe, perform honorable deeds, encourage Truth, and recommend patience. 
104|1| How awful [will it be] for every backbiting slanderer 
104|2| who hoards wealth and keeps on adding to it! 
104|3| He reckons that his money will make him immortal. 
104|4| Nevertheless he will be flung into the Bonecrusher! 
104|5| What will make you realize what the Bonecrusher is? 
104|6| [It is] God´s kindled fire 
104|7| which leaps up to clutch at one´s vitals. 
104|8| It will be vaulted over them 
104|9| in outstretched columns. 
105|1| Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with the owners of the Elephant? 
105|2| Did He not cause their plan to miscarry, 
105|3| and sent birds in flocks against them 
105|4| which threw stamped clay pellets at them? 
105|5| It left them just like chewed-up chaff. 
106|1| In dealing with the Quraysh, 
106|2| for their preparations to travel in winter and in summer; 
106|3| let them worship the Lord of this House 
106|4| Who feeds them against famine and secures them from fear. 
107|1| Have you seen someone who rejects religion? 
107|2| That is the person who pushes the orphan aside 
107|3| and does not promote feeding the needy. 
107|4| It will be too bad for the prayerful 
107|5| who are absent-minded as they pray, 
107|6| who aim to be noticed 
107|7| while they hold back contributions. 
108|1| We have given you plenty, 
108|2| so pray to your Lord and sacrifice 
108|3| since your opponent is the one who will be lopped off. 
109|1| SAY: "O disbelievers! 
109|2| I do not serve what you serve 
109|3| nor are you serving what I serve! 
109|4| I will not worship what you have worshipped, 
109|5| neither will you worship what I worship. 
109|6| You have your religion while I have my religion. 
110|1| When God´s support comes as well as victory, 
110|2| and you see mankind entering God´s religion in droves; 
110|3| then hymn your Lord´s praise and beg Him for forgiveness, since He is so Relenting! 
111|1| May Abo-Lahab´s both hands waste away and may he waste away [as well]! 
111|2| His wealth and what he´s earned will never profit him: 
111|3| he´ll roast in a fire with a flame; 
111|4| while his wife who carries kindling around 
111|5| will have a palm-fiber rope around her neck. 
112|1| SAY: "God is Unique! 
112|2| God is the Source [for everything]; 
112|3| He has not fathered anyone nor was He fathered, 
112|4| and there is nothing comparable to Him!" 
113|1| SAY: "I take refuge with the Lord of Dawn 
113|2| from the mischief which He has created, 
113|3| and from the evil of dusk as it settles down, 
113|4| and from the mischief of women spitting on knots 
113|5| and from the evil of some envier when he envies." 
114|1| SAY: "I take refuge with the Lord of Mankind, 
114|2| the King of Mankind, 
114|3| the God of Mankind, 
114|4| from the evil of the stealthy Whisperer 
114|5| who whispers in the breasts of Mankind, 
114|6| whether among sprites or Mankind.

